# AGENTS.md — {{name}}

## Purpose
This project was forged by the **Foundry Software Factory**. It follows the VoidZero ecosystem standard.

## Stack
- **Framework**: Astro (island architecture, zero JS by default)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/vite`, CSS-first config)
- **CSS**: Lightning CSS (Rust-based transformer + minifier)
- **Lint/Format**: Biome
- **Testing**: Vitest
- **Deploy**: Cloudflare Pages (`pages_build_output_dir: dist`)

## VoidZero Standard
- `astro.config.mjs` uses `@tailwindcss/vite` + Lightning CSS
- `build.inlineStylesheets: "always"` — inlines per-page CSS for fastest LCP
- No `tailwind.config.ts` — Tailwind v4 uses CSS-first config (`@import "tailwindcss"` in `src/styles/global.css`)
- No PostCSS config needed — `@tailwindcss/vite` handles it

## Context
- **Project Name**: {{name}}
- **Standard**: Foundry Gold Standard (v1) + VoidZero ecosystem
- **Infrastructure**: Managed via `fnd` (Foundry Commander)
- **Backend services**: Use `@saas-maker/sdk` when linking to the fleet API.

## Key commands
```bash
pnpm dev      # astro dev (localhost:4321)
pnpm build    # astro build → dist/
pnpm preview  # astro preview
pnpm lint     # biome check .
pnpm test     # vitest run
```

## Standard Procedures for Agents

### 1. Code Changes
- Prefer Astro components (`.astro`) over React for content/static surfaces.
- Use React islands only where interactivity is needed (add `@astrojs/react` integration).
- Keep CSS in `src/styles/global.css` — Tailwind v4 utilities are the default.

### 2. Maintenance
- Run `fnd audit` inside this directory to verify compliance.
- Run `fnd fleet upgrade` to refresh devDependencies.
